Description: An alchemical potion concocted by mad scientists a thousand years dead. Some of the realm's more daring blacksmiths have applied the unnaturally viscous substance to a variety of weapons and found that it heightens the attributes of certain martial artifacts of ancient Allagan design. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.
Name: Lost Allagan Roborant

Description: An alchemical thread woven by mad scientists a thousand years dead. Some of the realm's more daring weavers have applied the unnaturally pliable substance to a variety of vestments and found that it heightens the attributes of certain martial artifacts of ancient Allagan design. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.
Name: Lost Allagan Twine

Description: An alchemical potion concocted by mad scientists a thousand years dead. Some of the realm's more daring goldsmiths have applied the unnaturally illuminated substance to a variety of gems and found that it heightens the attributes of certain martial artifacts of ancient Allagan design. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.
Name: Lost Allagan Glaze

Description: A note of promise received from Rowena for the delivery of Allagan tomestones of creation or poetics. However, due to the House of Splendors changing its policies, it is now worth less than the paper on which it is scribed.
Name: Rowena's Token (Creation)

Description: Though considerably different in construction, Garlond Ironworks engineers insist this bulky contraption serves the same purpose as a traditional tomestone, and is merely of an earlier, less efficient design. This particular variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.
Name: Early Model Tomestone

Description: The Kojin carve, from shell, idols such as this one to present as offerings to their exalted Lord of the Revel, Susano.
Name: Revel Totem

Description: This pulsating metal idol forged in the likeness of the primal Lakshmi is thought to be employed by the Ananta in forbidden summoning ceremonies.
Name: Bliss Totem

Description:

Two lenses can be traded for special headgear.
Name: Deltascape Lens

Description:

Four shafts can be traded for special body gear.

Description:

Description:

Description: A uniquely crafted chain discovered in the Deltascape. Alas, advancements in trouser technology have rendered it worthless.
Name: Deltascape Chain

Description:
A uniquely crafted bolt discovered in the Deltascape.

One bolt can be traded for a special accessory.
Name: Deltascape Bolt

Name: Deltascape Crystalloid

Description: The blade from a sword used by the Lord of the Revel himself. Despite being long removed from its hilt, the steel still shudders with unseen magicks.
Name: Blade of Revelry

Description: A long sheet of translucent cloth taken from the robes worn by the Lady of the Bliss. In addition with being unnaturally lightweight, the shroud tingles the skin when touched.
